questions.reload_page_q: How do I reload a page?
questions.reload_page_a1: Get ready for some page-refreshing wisdom! We're about to dive into the magical world of reloading web pages. Here are some techniques:
questions.reload_page_a2: Press the F5 key or Ctrl + R (Windows/Linux) or Command + R (Mac) to manually reload the current page.
questions.reload_page_a3: Click the reload button in your browser. It usually looks like a circular arrow and is typically located in the address bar.
questions.reload_page_a4: Use JavaScript to reload the page programmatically: location.reload();
questions.return_policy_a:
We offer digital media (software) that can be used instantly after a purchase has been made. There is no “trial” or “grace period” after purchasing any product which means all sales are final. Once you have purchased the software, there is no way to “return” it.

It is a member’s responsibility to cancel any payment. If you decide to stop the membership and discontinue using our Products, remember to login to your PayPal and cancel the Authorization.

There will be no refund for members that forget to cancel their subscription.

cards.contentText: The unique stripes of zebras make them one of the animals most familiar to people.
cards.contentTextLong: The unique stripes of zebras make them one of the animals most familiar to people. They occur in a variety of habitats, such as grasslands, savannas, woodlands, thorny scrublands, mountains, and coastal hills. Various anthropogenic factors have had a severe impact on zebra populations, in particular hunting for skins and habitat destruction. Grévy's zebra and the mountain zebra are endangered. While plains zebras are much more plentiful, one subspecies, the quagga.
